||attachment:AlderHall.jpg||
'''Alder Hall''' is the western-most unit of the three-building UC Davis residence hall complex known as ["Segundo North"]. Built in 2003, Segundo North is located in the northwest quadrant of campus; double occupancy rooms in these buildings are grouped in clusters of four with a shared bathroom. In 2004, Alder 2 became home to the African-African American Academic Theme Program.
